1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Bug Bunny is a local-first proof console for authorized Web research.
It works with local labs, owned systems, and explicitly authorized in-scope
targets, including HackerOne, Bugcrowd, and Intigriti programs.

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Each account contributes its own DevTools cURL capture.
Tokens, object IDs, URLs, markers, and bodies stay ephemeral.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:36,000
The redaction preview confirms one endpoint shape, one changed locator,
and two distinct sessions before any traffic is sent.

4
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Bug Bunny proves B→B and A→A, then derives B→A by changing only the session.
A's marker appears under B, so execution stops at 3 of 4 requests.

5
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:05,000
The write-once receipt keeps only hashes, outcome booleans, timing,
network controls, and integrity metadata. Optional AI review is model-configurable.

6
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:18,680
AI can challenge the redacted evidence but never controls the verdict.
GPT-5.6 Sol helped turn a hard-coded IDOR demo into a structural cURL parser,
ephemeral-secret boundary, four-request verdict gate, and negative fixtures.
